Method Detail

deleteDir

protected static boolean deleteDir(java.io.File dir)
Deletes all files and subdirectories under dir. (method obtained from the Java developers almanac) Will remove the File instance dir (which should be a directory) and all files and subdirectories under dir. Will do nothing if dir is not a directory.

Parameters:
dir - an instance of File which should be a directory.
Returns:
true if all deletions were successful. If a deletion fails, the method stops attempting to delete and returns false.

makeBBOBdirs

public static boolean makeBBOBdirs(java.lang.String outputPath,
                                   boolean overwrite)
Creates required directories which will contain the data. This method creates the directories data_f1 to data_f24, and data_f101 to data_f130 for the noisy functions in the folder designated by the String outputPath.

Parameters:
outputPath - folder name in which the directories will be created
overwrite - if true, any former directories are deleted and recreated, if false and a directory exists at outputPath, nothing is changed and false returned
Returns:
true if the directories could be created or if they existed already, false otherwise

initBBOB

public double initBBOB(int funcId,
                       int instanceId,
                       int dim,
                       java.lang.String datapath,
                       JNIfgeneric.Params optParams)
Initializes the BBOB C backend. Has to be called each time any of the parameters (e.g. dimensions, functionID) changes; do not forget to call exitBBOB() before again calling initialize.

Returns:
the target function value of the specified fitness function

exitBBOB

public double exitBBOB()
Closes down the BBOB C backend initiated by initialize.

Returns:
the best true fitness value ever obtained

getBest

public double getBest()
Returns the best function value obtained so far. If any search points have been evaluated already (see evaluate()), the current best value is returned, otherwise it is the value DBL_MAX in C. Is the same as getFbest().

Returns:
the best function value obtained so far.

getFbest

public double getFbest()
Returns the best function value obtained so far. If any search points have been evaluated already (see evaluate()), the current best value is returned, otherwise it is the value DBL_MAX in C. Is the same as getBest().

Returns:
the best function value obtained so far.

getEvaluations

public double getEvaluations()
Returns the number of function since initialize() was called.

Returns:
the number of function evaluations since initialize() was called.

setNoiseSeed

public void setNoiseSeed(int seed)
Sets the noise random seed for the noisy functions. This function is provided for comparing the values of noisy functions for different implementation of fgeneric.

unif

public void unif(double[] r,
                 int N,
                 int inseed)
Provides with a uniform random value generator. This function is provided for comparing the values of functions for different implementation of fgeneric. It fills the input argument r with double values comprised between 0 and 1.

Parameters:
r - a double array to be filled (size must be larger than N)
N - an integer giving the number of random doubles to put in r
inseed - an integer seed

evaluate

public double evaluate(double[] X)
Returns the fitness value of X. X is a double array representing the decision variable vector. The search interval for X is [-5, 5] in each component. evalute(X) will return a reasonable value nonetheless for any real-valued X. Occasionally data are written in the data files.

Parameters:
X - decision variable vector
Returns:
the objective function value for the given search point
